<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,1322,1817]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,298,1466,1492]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">Habitat.</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[304,563,1467,1493]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1868" box="[304,439,1467,1492]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Limnogonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Limnogonus</taxonomicName>
a. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Drake &amp; Harris" authorityYear="1933" box="[472,563,1467,1493]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Limnogonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aduncus">aduncus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
has usually been found in the margins of pools, ponds and lagoons exposed to sunlight and with floating, emergent or submerged vegetation (
<bibRefCitation author="Melo, A. L. de &amp; Nieser, N." box="[848,1082,1503,1529]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="43 - 49" refId="ref52862" refString="Melo, A. L. de &amp; Nieser, N. (2004) Faunistical notes on aquatic Heteroptera of Minas Gerais (Brazil): an annotated list of Gerromorpha and Nepomorpha collected near Januaria, MG. Lundiana, 5, 43 - 49." type="journal article" year="2004">Melo &amp; Nieser 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pereira, D. L. V. &amp; Melo, A. L." box="[1092,1329,1503,1529]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="643 - 648" refId="ref55645" refString="Pereira, D. L. V. &amp; Melo, A. L. (2007) Aquatic and semiaquatic Heteroptera (Insecta) from Pitinga, Amazonas, Brazil. Acta Amazonica, 37, 643 - 648. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0044 - 59672007000400021" type="journal article" year="2007">Pereira &amp; Melo 2007</bibRefCitation>
; Molano-Rendón 
<emphasis box="[246,302,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">et al.</emphasis>
2008; 
<bibRefCitation author="Torres, P. L. M. &amp; Mazzucconi, S. A. &amp; Michat, M. C. &amp; Bachmann, A. O." box="[380,582,1539,1565]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="127 - 144" refId="ref58650" refString="Torres, P. L. M., Mazzucconi, S. A., Michat, M. C. &amp; Bachmann, A. O. (2008) Los coleopteros y heteropteros acuaticos del Parque Nacional Calilegua (Provincia de Jujuy, Argentina). Revista de la Sociedad Entomologica Argentina, 67 (1 - 2), 127 - 144." type="journal article" year="2008">
Torres 
<emphasis box="[459,516,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Moreira, F. F. F. &amp; Alecrim, V. P. &amp; Ribeiro, J. R. I. &amp; Nessimian, J. L." box="[594,827,1539,1565]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="269 - 279" refId="ref53715" refString="Moreira, F. F. F., Alecrim, V. P., Ribeiro, J. R. I. &amp; Nessimian, J. L. (2011 a) Identification key to the Gerridae (Insecta: Heteroptera: Gerromorpha) from the Amazon River floodplain, Brazil, with new records for the Brazilian Amazon. Zoologia, 28 (2), 269 - 279. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 1984 - 46702011000200018" type="journal article" year="2011">
Moreira 
<emphasis box="[692,748,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">et al.</emphasis>
2011a
</bibRefCitation>
), as well as in stagnant waterbodies near lotic habitats (overflows of streams; pools on banks of rivers; pools along dry streams) (
<bibRefCitation author="Roback, S. S." box="[1018,1174,1575,1601]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="211 - 215" refId="ref57109" refString="Roback, S. S. (1966) The Catherwood Foundation Peruvian-Amazon Expedition. VIII. Aquatic Hemiptera-Heteroptera. Monographs of the Academy of Natural Sciences of Philadelphia, 14, 211 - 215." type="journal article" year="1966">Roback 1966</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Melo, A. L. de &amp; Nieser, N." box="[1189,1432,1575,1601]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="43 - 49" refId="ref52862" refString="Melo, A. L. de &amp; Nieser, N. (2004) Faunistical notes on aquatic Heteroptera of Minas Gerais (Brazil): an annotated list of Gerromorpha and Nepomorpha collected near Januaria, MG. Lundiana, 5, 43 - 49." type="journal article" year="2004">Melo &amp; Nieser 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Moreno-R, C. &amp; Barbosa, J. F. &amp; Moreira, F. F. F." box="[151,399,1611,1637]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="985 - 1002" refId="ref54042" refString="Moreno-R, C., Molina-J, W., Barbosa, J. F. &amp; Moreira, F. F. F. (2018) Aquatic and semiaquatic bugs (Insecta, Hemiptera, Heteroptera) from Toluviejo Municipality, Sucre Department, Caribbean region of Colombia. Check List, 14 (6), 985 - 1002. https: // doi. org / 10.15560 / 14.6.985" type="journal article" year="2018">
Moreno-R 
<emphasis box="[275,331,1611,1637]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">et al.</emphasis>
2018
</bibRefCitation>
). This subspecies has also been collected in streams and rivers which are slow to moderately fast-flowing, with or without aquatic vegetation and in shaded or unshaded areas (
<bibRefCitation author="Mazzucconi, S. A. &amp; Bachmann, A. O." box="[1071,1431,1646,1673]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="363 - 370" refId="ref52609" refString="Mazzucconi, S. A. &amp; Bachmann, A. O. (1995) Geographic distribution of the Gerridae in Argentina (Insecta, Heteroptera). Insecta Mundi, 9, 363 - 370." type="journal article" year="1995">Mazzucconi &amp; Bachmann 1995</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Melo, A. L. de &amp; Nieser, N." box="[151,386,1683,1709]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="43 - 49" refId="ref52862" refString="Melo, A. L. de &amp; Nieser, N. (2004) Faunistical notes on aquatic Heteroptera of Minas Gerais (Brazil): an annotated list of Gerromorpha and Nepomorpha collected near Januaria, MG. Lundiana, 5, 43 - 49." type="journal article" year="2004">Melo &amp; Nieser 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Pereira, D. L. V. &amp; Melo, A. L." box="[397,637,1683,1709]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="643 - 648" refId="ref55645" refString="Pereira, D. L. V. &amp; Melo, A. L. (2007) Aquatic and semiaquatic Heteroptera (Insecta) from Pitinga, Amazonas, Brazil. Acta Amazonica, 37, 643 - 648. https: // doi. org / 10.1590 / S 0044 - 59672007000400021" type="journal article" year="2007">Pereira &amp; Melo 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Moreno-R, C. &amp; Barbosa, J. F. &amp; Moreira, F. F. F." box="[649,894,1683,1709]" pageId="15" pageNumber="466" pagination="985 - 1002" refId="ref54042" refString="Moreno-R, C., Molina-J, W., Barbosa, J. F. &amp; Moreira, F. F. F. (2018) Aquatic and semiaquatic bugs (Insecta, Hemiptera, Heteroptera) from Toluviejo Municipality, Sucre Department, Caribbean region of Colombia. Check List, 14 (6), 985 - 1002. https: // doi. org / 10.15560 / 14.6.985" type="journal article" year="2018">
Moreno-R 
<emphasis box="[773,829,1683,1709]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="466">et al.</emphasis>
2018
